   Feature Stories

   INEEL president: 'Accept change; stick with plan'
   INEEL leaders focused on the work-force restructuring plan and the
   Laboratory's path forward at an all-managers meeting April 10 at the
   Shilo Inn.
   -more-

   Lead assessor recommends VPP STAR for INEEL
   The Idaho National Engineering and Environmental Laboratory is about to
   become the first national laboratory to achieve VPP STAR status.
   -more-

   A commitment kept
   On April 20, INEEL employees helped the Department of Energy keep a
   major commitment to the state of Idaho.
   -more-

   Removal of INEEL landmark Cold War facility complete
   A famous INEEL landmark is gone for good. Workers recently completed
   the removal of the last two buildings and a section of railroad track
   remaining from the Initial Engine Test facility (IET) at Test Area
   North.
   -more-
